  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Defending territories of rural communities in the departments of Huila and Tolima</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to promote the guarantee and respect of the rights of the peasants (small-scale farmers) of Cajamarca, Tolima and the department of Huila in the decisions that affect their territories, promoting differentiated approaches to the impacts that large-scale mining and hydroelectric projects have on peasant territories. It is a small initial project with the new organisation Siembra continuing the work previously supported in Tolima through Tierra Digna, who ceased to be a CAFOD partner.</narrative>
  </description>
